Package: ivdoctr
Title: Ensures Mutually Consistent Beliefs When Using Instrumental Variables
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Frank", "DiTraglia", email = "francis.ditraglia@economics.ox.ac.uk", role = "aut"),
    person("Camilo", "Garc\'ia-Jimeno", email = "cgarcia@frbchi.org", role = "aut"),
    person("Mallick", "Hossain", email = "emallickhossain@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")), 
    person("Alejandro", "Sanchez Becerra", email = "alesan@sas.upenn.edu", role = "aut"))
Description: Uses data and researcher's beliefs on measurement error and
    instrument endogeneity to generate the space of consistent beliefs across
    measurement error, instrument endogeneity, and instrumental relevance for 
    IV regressions. Package based on DiTraglia and Garc\'ia-Jimeno (2020) <doi:10.1080/07350015.2020.1753528>.
License: CC0
LazyData: TRUE
Depends: R (>= 2.10)
